                <h1>Understanding Types of Connective Tissue</h1>
                <p>Connective tissue plays a crucial role in the body, providing structure and support. There are several types, including loose connective tissue, which binds organs and supports small blood vessels; dense connective tissue, found in tendons and ligaments; adipose tissue for storage; and specialized forms like cartilage and bone that offer unique functions.</p>
